{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Bosnia and Herzegovina | country_link = Bosnia and Herzegovina | continent = Europe | map_image = Europe-Bosnia and Herzegovina.svg | map_caption = Location of Bosnia and Herzegovina | map_size = 200px | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +387 | international_prefix = 00 | trunk_prefix = 0 | regulator = [[Communications Regulatory Agency of Bosnia and Herzegovina|RAK]] | plan_membership = | nsn_length = | dial_plan_type = [[Telephone numbering plan|Open]] | number_format = 0XX XXX XXX | codes_list = }}
The [[List of country calling codes|country calling code]] of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] is '''+387'''.
[[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] received the +387 code following the breakup of the [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]] in 1992. (which had +38 as the country code).
An example for calling telephones in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] is as follows:
* 0 33 xxx xxx (within Sarajevo)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mtel.ba/Korisnicka-zona/Vijesti/Vijesti/a491-Besplatne-izmjene-pozivanja-u-fiksnoj-telefoniji.html|title=Besplatne izmjene pozivanja u fiksnoj telefoniji|last=|first=|date=|work=m:tel|access-date=2018-01-20|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=Serbian}}</ref> * 0 33 xxx xxx (within Bosnia and Herzegovina) * +387 33 xxx xxx (outside of Bosnia and Herzegovina)
This is a '''list of dialing codes in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]'''.
